WEBVTT

00:01.697 --> 00:03.742
[electronic dance music]

00:03.786 --> 00:06.615
[indistinct chatter]

00:06.658 --> 00:13.448
♪

00:23.675 --> 00:25.634
- [speaking German]

00:27.375 --> 00:28.376
- [speaking German]

00:29.812 --> 00:32.597
- And I'm the queen of England.

00:32.641 --> 00:34.382
- Your Majesty.

00:34.425 --> 00:41.345
♪

01:00.190 --> 01:01.539
- Thomas.

01:01.583 --> 01:02.714
- Tanja.

01:07.241 --> 01:09.808
So how long have you been
in Berlin, Thomas,

01:09.852 --> 01:13.290
throwing parties
you don't wanna attend?

01:13.334 --> 01:15.379
- Two years.

01:15.423 --> 01:17.555
- Artist?

01:17.599 --> 01:19.383
- Student.

01:19.427 --> 01:21.124
At Kunstgut.

01:26.434 --> 01:28.610
- You must have rich parents.

01:28.653 --> 01:32.135
I mean,
this quarter is very posh.

01:32.179 --> 01:33.789
- [clears throat]
- I didn't meant to--

01:33.832 --> 01:35.573
- It's fine.

01:35.617 --> 01:38.185
I've been running away
from that my whole life.

01:40.796 --> 01:42.580
- Good.

01:42.624 --> 01:43.929
- Yeah.

01:43.973 --> 01:47.585
My friend Noah,
it was his idea to celebrate.

01:47.629 --> 01:49.587
I got into DAAD.

01:49.631 --> 01:52.503
It's this fancy--
- I know what DAAD is.

01:52.547 --> 01:54.592
I have artist friends who'd
give up their kidney to get in.

01:54.636 --> 01:55.854
- [laughs] Yeah.

01:55.898 --> 01:59.902
My parents,
they aren't so enthusiastic.

01:59.945 --> 02:02.905
[pensive music]

02:02.948 --> 02:04.602
♪

02:04.646 --> 02:05.777
- You don't look like someone

02:05.821 --> 02:08.432
who cares
what your parents think.

02:10.347 --> 02:11.653
- I don't.

02:25.536 --> 02:26.798
- Late as usual.

02:26.842 --> 02:28.235
- If you say Thomas gets it

02:28.278 --> 02:29.627
from my side of the family,

02:29.671 --> 02:32.500
I'm gonna have Levinson
take you out to the alley.

02:32.543 --> 02:34.284
- Your dad was late
to our wedding.

02:34.328 --> 02:36.852
- By five minutes.
- [chuckles]

02:36.895 --> 02:38.593
[knock at door]

02:38.636 --> 02:40.595
Thomas?

02:49.778 --> 02:52.781
[scoffs] Oh, for God's sake.

02:52.824 --> 02:56.306
[suspenseful music]

02:56.350 --> 02:57.394
- Thomas?

02:57.438 --> 03:01.833
♪

03:01.877 --> 03:03.270
- [gags]

03:03.313 --> 03:05.228
[coughs]

03:05.272 --> 03:07.274
- Thomas!

03:07.317 --> 03:09.232
Gabriel!

03:09.276 --> 03:10.494
- [spluttering]

03:10.538 --> 03:11.756
- Gabriel!

03:11.800 --> 03:13.018
- Thomas! Thomas!

03:13.062 --> 03:14.629
- You've gotta help him.

03:14.672 --> 03:16.326
- Levinson, call an ambulance!

03:16.370 --> 03:19.938
- What's happening to him?
- I don't--I don't know!

03:19.982 --> 03:21.244
- Do something!

03:21.288 --> 03:22.245
Is he breathing?

03:22.289 --> 03:23.551
Please, hang on, baby.
- Thomas!

03:23.594 --> 03:24.943
Thomas!
- [crying] Thomas!

03:24.987 --> 03:31.211
♪

03:32.473 --> 03:35.345
- He had no cause to fire you.

03:35.389 --> 03:36.564
- Smit didn't need cause.

03:36.607 --> 03:38.696
He needed an opportunity,
and he took it.

03:38.740 --> 03:39.958
- Why's he have it out for you?

03:40.002 --> 03:42.700
- We had a joint case.

03:42.744 --> 03:45.050
An organized crime outfit
running a prostitution ring

03:45.094 --> 03:46.530
across Germany.

03:46.574 --> 03:49.054
That case made Smit's career.

03:49.098 --> 03:52.275
He arrested the ringleader
and was promoted.

03:52.319 --> 03:55.974
But I had reason to believe
that he was working both sides

03:56.018 --> 03:57.585
and paid off the right people.

03:57.628 --> 03:58.890
- You filed a report?
- [laughs]

03:58.934 --> 04:00.979
Damn right I did.

04:01.023 --> 04:04.461
It was supposed
to be confidential,

04:04.505 --> 04:06.507
but nothing happened.

04:06.550 --> 04:09.423
I was soon hired by Europol
and put it all behind me.

04:09.466 --> 04:11.555
But then, two years ago,
Smit joined Europol

04:11.599 --> 04:13.514
as a senior director.

04:13.557 --> 04:16.821
I knew it was a matter of time
before he came for me.

04:16.865 --> 04:18.040
- What a bastard.

04:18.083 --> 04:19.389
- I have two weeks left.

04:19.433 --> 04:20.999
I'm still fighting.

04:21.043 --> 04:22.392
[speaking German]

04:22.436 --> 04:25.830
In German, it means
"the song is not yet over."

04:28.616 --> 04:31.009
- Ambassador?
- Ambassador.

04:31.053 --> 04:33.011
- Uh, this is
the U.S. ambassador

04:33.055 --> 04:34.535
to Hungary, Frank DeLillo.

04:34.578 --> 04:36.406
- Katrin Jaeger,
our Europol liaison.

04:36.450 --> 04:37.538
- Katrin.
- Nice to meet you.

04:37.581 --> 04:38.626
And this is the U.S. ambassador

04:38.669 --> 04:39.931
to Germany, Amy Schwartz.

04:39.975 --> 04:41.977
Special Agent Jamie Kellett.

04:42.020 --> 04:43.979
- We need to speak
to Scott Forrester right away.

04:44.022 --> 04:46.982
[suspenseful music]

04:47.025 --> 04:48.549
[buttons beeping]

04:48.592 --> 04:50.464
[door buzzes]

04:56.600 --> 04:59.429
- I've never had one ambassador
in my office,

04:59.473 --> 05:01.344
much less two.

05:01.388 --> 05:02.563
And since you're here
in person,

05:02.606 --> 05:03.955
I'm guessing
you need something urgently?

05:03.999 --> 05:05.870
- And with discretion.

05:05.914 --> 05:08.090
- An American art student
studying in Berlin

05:08.133 --> 05:11.049
was found unresponsive
this afternoon.

05:11.093 --> 05:12.877
Drug overdose.

05:12.921 --> 05:14.444
- Dead?
- Hospitalized.

05:14.488 --> 05:16.490
In critical condition.

05:16.533 --> 05:17.969
- Well, I'm sorry to hear that,

05:18.013 --> 05:19.884
but this sounds like a job
for Bundespolizei.

05:19.928 --> 05:22.974
- The father of the boy
is Gabriel Watts.

05:24.498 --> 05:25.760
- The billionaire.

05:25.803 --> 05:27.327
- And he wants answers.

05:30.721 --> 05:32.027
- Oh, well, I'm sorry

05:32.070 --> 05:33.985
to waste your time,
ambassadors,

05:34.029 --> 05:36.510
but we're not a rich man's
personal detective serv--

05:36.553 --> 05:39.121
- This would be
a personal favor

05:39.164 --> 05:40.775
to the president
of the United States,

05:40.818 --> 05:42.385
who called me directly
this morning.

05:46.868 --> 05:50.132
If you need further convincing,

05:50.175 --> 05:52.874
I'm happy to phone the director
of the FBI.

05:52.917 --> 05:59.881
♪

05:59.924 --> 06:01.839
- You'll receive
any assistance you need

06:01.883 --> 06:04.799
from the German National Police
in Berlin.

06:13.677 --> 06:16.680
- Thomas Watts,
a 19-year-old kid found OD'd

06:16.724 --> 06:20.380
in his apartment in Berlin
two days before his graduation.

06:22.251 --> 06:24.558
His parents flew in
from Palo Alto.

06:24.601 --> 06:26.037
Thomas was supposed
to meet them for lunch.

06:26.081 --> 06:28.083
They went to his apartment
when he didn't show.

06:28.126 --> 06:30.433
If they had arrived
five minutes later,

06:30.477 --> 06:31.608
their son would've been dead.

06:31.652 --> 06:33.915
- Zero posts.
Thousands of followers.

06:33.958 --> 06:35.438
Mostly likely spillover traffic

06:35.482 --> 06:37.440
from his dad's social media
footprint.

06:37.484 --> 06:39.790
Gabriel Watts,
founder of Force Innovation.

06:39.834 --> 06:41.096
Seventh richest person
in the world

06:41.139 --> 06:44.229
with a net worth
of $62.5 billion.

06:44.273 --> 06:46.144
- Imagine having to live up
to all that.

06:46.188 --> 06:48.669
- A privileged kid OD'ing
isn't exactly uncommon.

06:48.712 --> 06:50.714
Not to speak out of turn,
but why are we on this?

06:50.758 --> 06:53.151
- $62.5 billion.

06:53.195 --> 06:54.631
That's why.

06:54.675 --> 06:56.111
I do not like this, either,
so let's just figure out

06:56.154 --> 06:58.243
where the kid got the drugs
as soon as possible

06:58.287 --> 06:59.767
and be done with it.

06:59.810 --> 07:01.856
- I've just spoken
with the BKA in Berlin.

07:01.899 --> 07:03.988
They are expecting us.

07:04.032 --> 07:10.995
♪

07:11.039 --> 07:12.954
- [speaking German]

07:12.997 --> 07:14.390
- Danke, Leon.

07:14.434 --> 07:16.827
This is Special Agent
Scott Forrester of the FBI,

07:16.871 --> 07:19.221
Special Agents Kellett,
Raines, and Vo.

07:19.264 --> 07:21.266
- Leon Honsel,
Senior Chief Inspector,

07:21.310 --> 07:22.572
Berlin Police.

07:22.616 --> 07:24.095
You may use our conference room

07:24.139 --> 07:25.488
if that satisfies you.

07:25.532 --> 07:27.751
- It does.
- This way, please.

07:27.795 --> 07:29.753
- How long have you worked
in Narcotics?

07:29.797 --> 07:31.668
- Five years,
as of one month ago.

07:31.712 --> 07:34.671
Six months
as Senior Chief Inspector.

07:34.715 --> 07:37.587
- Any word on Thomas Watts'
toxicology report?

07:37.631 --> 07:40.111
- Yes, he had oxycodone
in his system

07:40.155 --> 07:43.071
and trace amounts of fentanyl.

07:43.114 --> 07:44.855
Fentanyl is quite rare here.

07:44.899 --> 07:46.640
We call it "America's problem."

07:46.683 --> 07:48.598
- Fentanyl
is a supplier's dream:

07:48.642 --> 07:49.686
a fraction of the cost

07:49.730 --> 07:51.209
and exponentially
more addictive.

07:51.253 --> 07:53.995
- Have you seen a spike
in fentanyl ODs in Germany?

07:54.038 --> 07:55.475
- No, no.

07:55.518 --> 07:58.739
Thomas Watts' exposure
was an anomaly, I assure you.

07:58.782 --> 08:00.001
Here we are.

08:04.309 --> 08:08.749
- Danke, Leon.
- [speaking German]

08:08.792 --> 08:10.577
- All right.
Everybody, unload here.

08:10.620 --> 08:13.318
Raines, Vo, I want you to head
to Thomas' apartment.

08:13.362 --> 08:15.669
See what you can find
that might point to a dealer.

08:15.712 --> 08:17.671
Friends, neighbors,
scraps of paper,

08:17.714 --> 08:20.804
anything that BPOL already has,
I wanna know about it.

08:20.848 --> 08:22.153
Kellett, you and me are gonna
head to the hospital

08:22.197 --> 08:23.633
to interview the parents.

08:23.677 --> 08:26.157
And Jaeger,
if you've got contacts outside

08:26.201 --> 08:29.160
of Bundespolizei,
now would be the time.

08:29.204 --> 08:32.163
Senior Chief Inspector Honsel
seemed a little quick to deny

08:32.207 --> 08:34.339
fentanyl overdoses
are happening here.

08:34.383 --> 08:35.993
- I caught that as well.

08:36.037 --> 08:37.299
I'll reach out
to my counterparts

08:37.342 --> 08:38.648
at Interpol in Berlin, okay?

08:38.692 --> 08:41.172
- Okay.

08:41.216 --> 08:42.870
You ready?

08:50.921 --> 08:53.750
[knock at door]
Mr. and Mrs. Watts?

08:53.794 --> 08:55.186
I'm Special Agent
Scott Forrester.

08:55.230 --> 08:57.014
This is Special Agent
Jamie Kellett with the FBI.

08:57.058 --> 08:59.669
- Finally. Uh, Gabriel Watts.

08:59.713 --> 09:01.584
My wife, Marian.

09:01.628 --> 09:03.847
[door slams]

09:03.891 --> 09:06.676
And this is, uh, Mark Levinson,
personal security.

09:06.720 --> 09:08.330
He's been with the family
for 15 years.

09:08.373 --> 09:11.072
He's cleared to hear anything
pertaining to--

09:11.115 --> 09:13.074
- Cleared by whom?

09:13.117 --> 09:14.902
- By me.

09:14.945 --> 09:17.600
- I'm sorry this happened
to Thomas, Mrs. Watts.

09:17.644 --> 09:19.036
- You'll find who poisoned him?

09:19.080 --> 09:20.647
- That's why we're here.

09:20.690 --> 09:22.300
- I know what you're thinking.

09:22.344 --> 09:24.825
Affluent son
rebels against his parents,

09:24.868 --> 09:26.870
but that's not Thomas.

09:26.914 --> 09:28.219
He never caused us trouble.

09:28.263 --> 09:31.222
He never dabbled in drugs.

09:31.266 --> 09:32.876
He never asked for a dime.

09:32.920 --> 09:34.922
- Not that we didn't want
to give him more.

09:34.965 --> 09:36.271
You know, I tried.

09:36.314 --> 09:37.925
I begged him.

09:37.968 --> 09:39.230
When he said he was moving
to Berlin,

09:39.274 --> 09:41.363
I said, "Private security.

09:41.406 --> 09:44.366
Personal driver."

09:44.409 --> 09:46.237
Thomas rejected
all those things.

09:46.281 --> 09:47.369
He said
that he was an adult now

09:47.412 --> 09:50.372
and he could make
his own decisions.

09:51.939 --> 09:54.245
- He craved normalcy.

09:54.289 --> 09:56.204
- You have kids?

09:56.247 --> 09:58.902
- No.

09:58.946 --> 10:01.122
- Listen to me when I tell you

10:01.165 --> 10:05.126
that you would give everything,
every dollar you have,

10:05.169 --> 10:07.215
every--every stitch
of clothing you own,

10:07.258 --> 10:12.220
every fiber of your being
to keep your son safe.

10:12.263 --> 10:15.266
And then he grows up
and you can't.

10:15.310 --> 10:17.878
[solemn music]

10:17.921 --> 10:20.184
- My parents
were very practical.

10:20.228 --> 10:23.231
So when Thomas was accepted
into art school,

10:23.274 --> 10:25.842
I convinced Gabriel
to let him go.

10:25.886 --> 10:27.278
- It was both of our decisions.

10:27.322 --> 10:29.629
It was the right thing to do.

10:32.327 --> 10:35.939
- We are just beginning
our investigation.

10:35.983 --> 10:37.288
But I have to ask,

10:37.332 --> 10:38.899
can either of you think
of anyone

10:38.942 --> 10:40.422
who would've targeted Thomas
specifically?

10:40.465 --> 10:41.684
- Why?

10:41.728 --> 10:42.903
- Personal grudge.

10:42.946 --> 10:46.776
To get to you, your money,
through your son?

10:46.820 --> 10:49.083
- No. No one.

10:49.126 --> 10:52.782
- Thomas makes friends
wherever he goes.

10:52.826 --> 10:59.354
♪

11:01.182 --> 11:04.185
- [speaking German]

11:07.884 --> 11:10.495
Ah, we haven't found evidence
of opioids on-site,

11:10.539 --> 11:14.021
but CSS are sending samples
to the lab for testing.

11:14.064 --> 11:15.022
- Security cameras?

11:15.065 --> 11:16.501
- The building has one camera

11:16.545 --> 11:19.766
in the lobby, and uh,
there are two security cameras

11:19.809 --> 11:21.898
in the foyer across the street.

11:21.942 --> 11:23.857
We have been using them
to identify the guests

11:23.900 --> 11:25.293
at the party.

11:25.336 --> 11:27.121
They're en route
to give statements.

11:27.164 --> 11:28.470
- We'll explore
in the meantime.

11:28.513 --> 11:30.341
- Oh, yes, yes, please.
Anything you need.

11:30.385 --> 11:33.344
[suspenseful music]

11:33.388 --> 11:40.395
♪

11:55.889 --> 11:58.543
- Raines, how many shirts
do you have in your closet?

11:58.587 --> 12:00.937
- Couple dozen.

12:00.981 --> 12:03.984
- More than this?

12:04.027 --> 12:07.030
- Witnesses are here in case
you would like to assist us

12:07.074 --> 12:08.379
in conducting the interviews.

12:08.423 --> 12:10.077
- We would.

12:12.906 --> 12:14.385
- Finn Mueller.

12:14.429 --> 12:16.039
Graduated
from Berlin Art Institute

12:16.083 --> 12:17.040
seven years ago.

12:17.084 --> 12:18.172
Now living in Munich.

12:18.215 --> 12:19.826
What were you doing
at a party here?

12:19.869 --> 12:21.436
- I work for DAAD.

12:21.479 --> 12:23.090
Yes, in Munich.

12:23.133 --> 12:25.135
[laughs]
Maybe you don't know it.

12:25.179 --> 12:27.921
- Deutscher Akademischer
Austauschdienst.

12:27.964 --> 12:30.184
German Academic
Exchange Service.

12:30.227 --> 12:33.274
I know it.
- Ah, yeah. Excuse me.

12:33.317 --> 12:35.493
I work, uh, in admissions
with DAAD.

12:35.537 --> 12:38.018
He was--he was quite
an impressive artist.

12:38.061 --> 12:40.063
I advocated for Thomas,
so when he was accepted,

12:40.107 --> 12:41.891
I came to Berlin
to congratulate him.

12:41.935 --> 12:44.154
- How long did you stay?
- Half hour.

12:44.198 --> 12:45.460
Like you said,
I wasn't going to hang around

12:45.503 --> 12:47.157
university students all night.

12:47.201 --> 12:50.247
- Did you observe any drug use
at the party?

12:50.291 --> 12:53.511
- With artists there's always
that possibility.

12:53.555 --> 12:56.253
I did not observe it directly,
though, no.

12:58.386 --> 13:01.041
- None of it makes sense.
Tom is so straight-laced.

13:01.084 --> 13:04.044
One beer and he's passed out
on the couch.

13:04.087 --> 13:05.088
You know his parents
won't let me

13:05.132 --> 13:06.394
into the hospital to see him?

13:06.437 --> 13:08.439
Family only. Unbelievable.

13:08.483 --> 13:10.137
I'm Thomas' closest friend.

13:10.180 --> 13:12.879
- How'd you meet?
- First week of school.

13:12.922 --> 13:14.315
Tom was introverted.

13:14.358 --> 13:15.882
Never told any of us
his last name

13:15.925 --> 13:17.448
or whose son he was.

13:17.492 --> 13:18.885
And we didn't care.

13:18.928 --> 13:21.539
He was just Tom, you know?

13:21.583 --> 13:23.106
Eventually,
he admitted his dad bought him

13:23.150 --> 13:24.978
this posh Mitte flat.

13:25.021 --> 13:27.110
Made me swear
to keep it a secret.

13:27.154 --> 13:29.243
- What can you tell us
about the party?

13:29.286 --> 13:32.289
- It was just a few friends
celebrating.

13:32.333 --> 13:34.291
- There were over 100 photos
from that night

13:34.335 --> 13:36.206
tagged at this location.

13:36.250 --> 13:37.860
- You didn't let me finish.

13:37.904 --> 13:40.907
I tried to keep things small.

13:40.950 --> 13:43.039
12 people maximum.

13:43.083 --> 13:48.088
But then social media,
and a party is a party.

13:48.131 --> 13:50.046
Is it not this way everywhere?

13:53.702 --> 13:59.142
♪

13:59.186 --> 14:00.883
It was a blank canvas
before the party.

14:00.927 --> 14:02.015
I'm sure of it.

14:03.712 --> 14:06.410
- You know her?

14:06.454 --> 14:09.196
- Tom was talking to a girl.

14:09.239 --> 14:10.501
I didn't recognize her,

14:10.545 --> 14:12.416
but she had dark hair
like that sketch.

14:12.460 --> 14:18.901
And she was wearing black,
how do you say, um, army boots.

14:18.945 --> 14:22.905
She seemed older. Maybe 25.

14:22.949 --> 14:24.559
I saw them come in here,
but I only caught

14:24.602 --> 14:27.475
the back of her head.

14:27.518 --> 14:28.911
- When did they return?

14:28.955 --> 14:30.130
- They didn't.

14:30.173 --> 14:33.002
It is so rare for Thomas
to be with a girl,

14:33.046 --> 14:34.438
much less a stranger.

14:34.482 --> 14:37.702
I wasn't going
to throw off his vibe.

14:37.746 --> 14:41.445
But when he didn't come home...

14:41.489 --> 14:42.446
- Home?

14:42.490 --> 14:44.187
- I meant to say, um--

14:44.231 --> 14:48.061
- Noah, I know
Tom doesn't live here.

14:48.104 --> 14:50.672
Bureau's empty, no laptop,
no person effects.

14:50.715 --> 14:52.369
Only art supplies.

14:52.413 --> 14:55.895
He may paint here,
but he doesn't live here.

14:57.766 --> 15:00.203
- Tom has a flat in Kreuzberg.

15:00.247 --> 15:01.552
He said his parents
would never let him live

15:01.596 --> 15:02.553
in that quarter.

15:02.597 --> 15:09.604
♪

15:15.697 --> 15:18.613
- This is Thomas' idea
of slumming it?

15:23.226 --> 15:24.401
- Look in all the drawers.

15:24.445 --> 15:28.231
Don't stop
until you find something.

15:28.275 --> 15:31.060
- There's nothing here.

15:31.104 --> 15:33.149
- Tear this place apart
if you have to.

15:33.193 --> 15:36.152
[tense music]

15:36.196 --> 15:43.203
♪

16:01.134 --> 16:04.137
[objects clattering]

16:13.624 --> 16:15.452
- Drop the gun.

16:15.496 --> 16:20.327
♪

16:20.370 --> 16:23.156
- Drop it.

16:33.383 --> 16:35.907
- Scott Forrester
and Jamie Kellett, FBI.

16:35.951 --> 16:38.780
We are on official business
with Bundespolizei.

16:38.823 --> 16:40.912
Lower your weapons.

16:40.956 --> 16:42.740
[tense music]

16:42.784 --> 16:43.785
- Everybody, stand down.

16:43.828 --> 16:45.569
Put away the hardware.

16:45.613 --> 16:47.180
We're all on the same team.

16:47.223 --> 16:52.620
♪

16:52.663 --> 16:54.361
- What the hell is this?
What is going on?

16:54.404 --> 16:55.971
- These guys work
for Gray Desert.

16:56.015 --> 16:58.060
- Oh, man.
- It's nothing personal.

16:58.104 --> 17:00.062
- Gabriel Watts has employed
them for many years.

17:00.106 --> 17:02.064
He's asked for reassurances,
safeguards.

17:02.108 --> 17:03.718
- That's not how this works.

17:03.761 --> 17:06.199
- Well, my understanding is,
the FBI is here as guests

17:06.242 --> 17:08.984
to the German government,
correct?

17:09.028 --> 17:10.464
If you need confirmation,
I'd be happy to make--

17:10.507 --> 17:13.684
- They are contaminating
an avenue of investigation.

17:13.728 --> 17:15.947
- Tossing this place
is a damn raid.

17:15.991 --> 17:18.950
Any chance we have of finding
evidence is now gone.

17:18.994 --> 17:21.170
- I'm just following
Gabriel Watts' directives,

17:21.214 --> 17:22.345
same as you.

17:22.389 --> 17:24.217
- Same as me?
- We don't work for Watts.

17:24.260 --> 17:26.001
- I'll rephrase that.

17:26.045 --> 17:27.742
Just wanna find out
who gave Thomas

17:27.785 --> 17:29.048
a hot batch of OxyContin.

17:29.091 --> 17:30.745
That is our only agenda here.

17:33.052 --> 17:34.966
- Hey! Uh-uh.

17:35.010 --> 17:37.317
- Per Mr. Watts' instruction,

17:37.360 --> 17:39.667
Gray Desert
reviews everything first.

17:39.710 --> 17:41.321
Now, I'd be happy
to share our findings

17:41.364 --> 17:42.757
if you'll reciprocate.

17:42.800 --> 17:43.758
- The Berlin police--

17:43.801 --> 17:45.890
- Senior Chief Inspector Honsel

17:45.934 --> 17:47.414
gave us his consent.

17:47.457 --> 17:50.025
Electronic devices belonging
to Thomas

17:50.069 --> 17:52.375
are Gabriel Watts' extended
personal property.

17:52.419 --> 17:53.681
- Then maybe
you didn't hear us before.

17:53.724 --> 17:55.987
We do not work
for Gabriel Watts.

17:56.031 --> 17:58.729
- Then I suggest you take
that up directly with him.

18:02.994 --> 18:05.954
- You contacted
every politician that you know

18:05.997 --> 18:07.956
to bring in the FBI,
and then you went off

18:07.999 --> 18:09.871
and started
your own private investigation.

18:09.914 --> 18:11.220
- That's my son in there.

18:11.264 --> 18:13.266
I leveraged all resources
at my disposal

18:13.309 --> 18:16.138
to find out who did that
to my boy.

18:16.182 --> 18:17.966
Identify multiple
possible solutions.

18:18.009 --> 18:19.446
That's how you
increase productivity.

18:19.489 --> 18:20.969
That's how you innovate.

18:21.012 --> 18:22.144
- You're undermining
our investigation

18:22.188 --> 18:24.190
and slowing us down.

18:24.233 --> 18:26.366
- Gray Desert
will send that laptop

18:26.409 --> 18:27.889
and that phone to Tel Aviv.

18:27.932 --> 18:30.239
They will crack it, yes,
and they will be thorough,

18:30.283 --> 18:32.154
but it will take three days
minimum.

18:32.198 --> 18:34.983
We have an agent on our team
right now, here in Berlin,

18:35.026 --> 18:36.767
who will have them
spilling their secrets

18:36.811 --> 18:39.030
in one hour, guaranteed.

18:42.121 --> 18:43.948
- Give Agent Forrester
what he needs.

18:43.992 --> 18:44.993
- Sir,
the folks at Gray Desert--

18:45.036 --> 18:46.429
- Do it, Mark.

18:46.473 --> 18:53.175
♪

18:57.223 --> 19:00.748
- Ilse, thanks for meeting me.
- Always, Katrin.

19:00.791 --> 19:03.098
- You were at Bundespolizei
before Interpol, yes?

19:03.142 --> 19:04.099
- I was.

19:04.143 --> 19:05.187
- What can you tell me about

19:05.231 --> 19:07.189
Senior Chief Inspector
Leon Honsel?

19:07.233 --> 19:08.886
- He's not corrupt.

19:08.930 --> 19:11.846
Just in over his head
and desperate to please.

19:11.889 --> 19:13.239
- How so?

19:13.282 --> 19:15.241
- His father's in Parliament.

19:15.284 --> 19:16.633
- Say no more.

19:16.677 --> 19:19.810
- I've been considering
your American overdose.

19:21.334 --> 19:22.857
- What's this?

19:22.900 --> 19:24.859
- I've cross-referenced guests
at the party

19:24.902 --> 19:25.990
with previous arrests.

19:26.034 --> 19:27.818
- Yes, yes, yes.
We already did that.

19:27.862 --> 19:29.472
- Oh, I know, Katrin.

19:29.516 --> 19:34.347
So I cross-referenced guests
with previous hospitalizations.

19:34.390 --> 19:36.914
Maybe Thomas' supplier
is a user himself.

19:38.525 --> 19:40.483
And can lead you
to the drug lord.

19:40.527 --> 19:46.054
♪

19:46.097 --> 19:47.751
- Katrin.

19:47.795 --> 19:49.405
- Ugh, not now.

19:51.059 --> 19:52.974
- While you
are a Europol investigator,

19:53.017 --> 19:54.802
you still report to me.

19:54.845 --> 19:57.196
And that's what's missing:
reports.

19:59.459 --> 20:02.549
The United States' president
is personally asking Europol

20:02.592 --> 20:03.985
for updates on this case.

20:04.028 --> 20:07.249
I have nothing
to tell my supervisor.

20:07.293 --> 20:09.817
- Herr Smit,
I will say this clearly

20:09.860 --> 20:11.471
so there will be no mistake.

20:11.514 --> 20:16.302
This is my last case,
and I intend to solve it.

20:16.345 --> 20:18.042
Politics.

20:21.350 --> 20:22.917
- Thomas' laptop,

20:22.960 --> 20:24.919
completely vanilla
on the surface.

20:24.962 --> 20:27.269
Schoolwork, family photos.

20:27.313 --> 20:30.359
But then,
a one-key recovery partition

20:30.403 --> 20:33.928
he didn't want anyone to find
with active social media

20:33.971 --> 20:35.103
under a pseudonym.

20:35.146 --> 20:36.931
- Thomas wanted
to separate his talent

20:36.974 --> 20:38.280
from his last name.

20:38.324 --> 20:42.110
[suspenseful music]

20:42.153 --> 20:45.200
- Go back to his social media.

20:45.244 --> 20:47.985
Any new followers
after the party?

20:48.029 --> 20:49.248
- 37.

20:52.642 --> 20:54.862
- There.

20:54.905 --> 21:01.912
♪

21:13.359 --> 21:14.664
- Tanja Kessler.

21:14.708 --> 21:17.363
Graduated from Freie University
six years ago.

21:17.406 --> 21:19.190
She's an artist like Thomas,

21:19.234 --> 21:21.410
but doesn't seem to have had
as much success.

21:21.454 --> 21:22.585
- Got an address.

21:22.629 --> 21:29.853
♪

21:34.989 --> 21:36.643
- Berlin's supposed to be
a mecca for young artists,

21:36.686 --> 21:38.122
but it's unaffordable
unless you get accepted

21:38.166 --> 21:40.864
into a fancy residency
or you have rich parents.

21:40.908 --> 21:42.605
- Or talent.

21:45.216 --> 21:46.870
- I'm sorry. What's this about?

21:46.914 --> 21:48.002
- Thomas Watts.

21:48.045 --> 21:49.395
- How well did you know him?

21:49.438 --> 21:52.136
- We only met a couple
of nights ago.

21:52.180 --> 21:53.703
There was a party
at his apartment.

21:53.747 --> 21:55.009
Heard about it on Snap.

21:55.052 --> 21:57.011
- So you wandered
into a stranger's apartment

21:57.054 --> 21:58.708
and ended up talking
to a kid all night

21:58.752 --> 22:03.887
whose dad happens to be worth
what, $62 billion?

22:03.931 --> 22:06.542
- I knew none of that.

22:06.586 --> 22:09.502
- Tell us how you got talking.

22:09.545 --> 22:11.895
- Uh, I was on my way out.

22:11.939 --> 22:13.897
Party wasn't my taste.

22:13.941 --> 22:16.857
But then I looked over
and I see Thomas.

22:16.900 --> 22:18.772
He was just as bored as me.

22:21.514 --> 22:23.733
We had a really nice time.

22:23.777 --> 22:26.257
Or I had a really nice time.

22:26.301 --> 22:29.522
I thought I'd hear from him
after, but...

22:31.785 --> 22:33.482
- He's in the hospital.

22:33.526 --> 22:35.528
Overdosed.

22:35.571 --> 22:36.659
- What?

22:36.703 --> 22:38.531
- Just walk us through
what happened.

22:38.574 --> 22:39.880
- What, is he okay?

22:39.923 --> 22:41.490
- We don't know.

22:43.057 --> 22:45.581
- Um...

22:45.625 --> 22:47.888
Thomas told me he got
into DAAD.

22:47.931 --> 22:49.019
That might mean nothing to you,

22:49.063 --> 22:51.544
but it's a huge deal
for artists.

22:51.587 --> 22:54.068
So I said, "Let's celebrate."

22:54.111 --> 22:57.854
I meant drinks,
but he brought out drugs.

22:57.898 --> 22:59.943
- He did?

22:59.987 --> 23:00.944
- Yes.

23:00.988 --> 23:02.729
- Had you done oxys before?

23:02.772 --> 23:05.688
- [laughs] I won't pretend
to be a white flower.

23:08.212 --> 23:12.260
- Thomas, though,
he seemed conservative.

23:12.303 --> 23:13.827
I was surprised.

23:13.870 --> 23:16.699
But then he took out two pills,
and we each swallowed one.

23:16.743 --> 23:18.875
- Just one?

23:18.919 --> 23:21.051
- At the start.

23:21.095 --> 23:23.967
Then Thomas became manic.

23:24.011 --> 23:25.795
He started saying,
"I wanna draw you.

23:25.839 --> 23:27.841
Let me draw you."

23:27.884 --> 23:31.148
Thomas had his easel
and charcoals out.

23:31.192 --> 23:34.978
Then he took more
and more pills.

23:35.022 --> 23:36.806
I kept asking if he was okay,

23:36.850 --> 23:40.636
but he just kept drawing
like he was possessed.

23:40.680 --> 23:43.509
- So what, he got sick
and you just left?

23:43.552 --> 23:45.119
- No.

23:45.162 --> 23:46.555
The sun came up.

23:46.599 --> 23:47.817
Thomas said he was sleepy

23:47.861 --> 23:50.603
so I told him to call me,
and I went home.

23:54.694 --> 23:56.304
[exhales heavily]

23:56.347 --> 23:58.045
I liked him.

23:59.873 --> 24:01.831
You know that feeling
when you first meet someone

24:01.875 --> 24:04.530
and they just see you?

24:06.314 --> 24:08.316
- Sure.

24:08.359 --> 24:11.275
- You know how rare that is?

24:11.319 --> 24:13.190
- Did he tell you
where he got the drugs?

24:15.062 --> 24:17.020
- He said someone was in town
and hooked him up.

24:17.064 --> 24:20.807
♪

24:20.850 --> 24:23.026
- No misdemeanors, no unusual
credit card activity,

24:23.070 --> 24:24.550
no regular cash withdrawals.

24:24.593 --> 24:27.248
- Inherited some money
after her grandmother died.

24:27.291 --> 24:29.032
No employment history since.

24:29.076 --> 24:31.600
- She's pointing the finger
at someone outta of town

24:31.644 --> 24:33.863
who supplied Thomas
with the drugs, so...

24:33.907 --> 24:35.561
- Ah.

24:35.604 --> 24:36.649
- What?

24:36.692 --> 24:38.085
- Finn Mueller.

24:40.653 --> 24:42.611
He came in from Munich
to congratulate Thomas

24:42.655 --> 24:44.613
on his acceptance
to the art residency, correct?

24:44.657 --> 24:45.919
- That's what he said.

24:45.962 --> 24:48.704
- Well, Finn Mueller
has been in Berlin before.

24:51.925 --> 24:53.883
- You didn't tell us
that you overdosed in Berlin

24:53.927 --> 24:55.232
six months ago.

24:55.276 --> 24:57.147
Why keep that detail from us?

24:57.191 --> 24:59.280
- I knew you would react
like this.

24:59.323 --> 25:00.890
With judgment.

25:00.934 --> 25:03.937
I'm not a dopehead, okay?

25:03.980 --> 25:06.592
- Your toxicology report
said you had enough opioids

25:06.635 --> 25:08.158
in your system
to knock out a school bus,

25:08.202 --> 25:11.858
yet you survived because
you build up a tolerance.

25:11.901 --> 25:13.250
Tell us again
you're not a dopehead.

25:13.294 --> 25:15.209
- I was clean
for a whole year.

25:15.252 --> 25:16.950
Hardest thing I've ever done.

25:19.126 --> 25:21.215
Yeah, stress triggers relapses.

25:21.258 --> 25:24.697
I've a new job where
artists' futures depend on me.

25:24.740 --> 25:27.656
The pills...they helped.

25:27.700 --> 25:30.267
- You dropped by Thomas' house
to congratulate him, right?

25:30.311 --> 25:31.617
Did you try to help him too?

25:34.141 --> 25:37.840
- Every day I wake up,
my brain fights

25:37.884 --> 25:41.278
to deprive my body
of what feels like air.

25:41.322 --> 25:44.630
I would never pull anyone
into that.

25:48.982 --> 25:51.201
- The information you have

25:51.245 --> 25:53.943
could help us find whoever
did this to him.

25:57.730 --> 25:59.688
- Everything
works through apps now.

25:59.732 --> 26:01.037
By referral only.

26:01.081 --> 26:03.649
Super high-end,
as easy as Uber Eats.

26:03.692 --> 26:05.346
- And you
were Thomas' referral?

26:05.389 --> 26:06.477
- [scoffs]

26:06.521 --> 26:08.828
No. I just told you. No.

26:08.871 --> 26:11.918
- We're gonna need that app.

26:11.961 --> 26:13.180
- It's Schwarzer Pinguin.

26:13.223 --> 26:14.660
"Black Penguin" in English.

26:14.703 --> 26:16.400
But it's useless
without a code.

26:16.444 --> 26:19.708
Every week,
they change the referral code.

26:19.752 --> 26:21.144
Without it, you can order
all you want,

26:21.188 --> 26:22.668
but you won't get a response.

26:22.711 --> 26:24.147
- So get the code for us.

26:24.191 --> 26:30.414
♪

26:30.458 --> 26:33.287
- There's no drug-ordering app
on either side of the partition

26:33.330 --> 26:34.331
on Thomas' laptop.

26:34.375 --> 26:35.550
- On his phone then?

26:35.594 --> 26:37.421
- The bodyguard
only handed us a laptop.

26:37.465 --> 26:39.772
- What?

26:39.815 --> 26:42.383
Oh, I'm getting
real tired of this.

26:42.426 --> 26:45.821
[people speaking German]
[monitor beeping rapidly]

26:45.865 --> 26:48.824
[tense music]

26:48.868 --> 26:55.788
♪

27:04.492 --> 27:06.363
- [gasps]

27:06.407 --> 27:09.889
[crying]

27:09.932 --> 27:11.194
- Stand back.

27:16.156 --> 27:19.202
- Again.

27:19.246 --> 27:21.422
[sustained high-pitched tone]

27:21.465 --> 27:24.294
- [sobs] Oh, no.

27:24.338 --> 27:27.036
[both crying]

27:27.080 --> 27:28.429
Oh, please, no.

27:28.472 --> 27:31.737
Please. Please, no.

27:31.780 --> 27:33.129
No.

27:33.173 --> 27:36.916
[sobbing]

27:41.485 --> 27:44.445
- [crying]

27:44.488 --> 27:47.448
[somber music]

27:47.491 --> 27:54.498
♪

28:03.682 --> 28:06.032
- We are so sorry
for your loss, Mr. Watts.

28:08.948 --> 28:10.079
And we're gonna
do everything we can

28:10.123 --> 28:13.822
to find
the persons responsible.

28:13.866 --> 28:17.608
- I, uh, Marian and I,

28:17.652 --> 28:21.047
we appreciate what you did
to help, but...

28:21.090 --> 28:23.092
my team will handle it
from here.

28:23.136 --> 28:26.487
[tense music]

28:26.530 --> 28:33.537
♪

28:39.065 --> 28:40.544
- Frankly,
I thought you'd be pleased

28:40.588 --> 28:41.676
with this development.

28:41.720 --> 28:42.808
Just this morning,
you wanted to pawn

28:42.851 --> 28:44.635
this case off
to the Bundespolizei.

28:44.679 --> 28:46.681
- Yeah, well, that was before
a 19-year-old kid

28:46.725 --> 28:48.074
with his whole life ahead
of him died in front--

28:48.117 --> 28:49.815
- BPOL is more than capable

28:49.858 --> 28:51.599
of continuing
this investigation

28:51.642 --> 28:52.600
without all of your--

28:52.643 --> 28:53.775
- Not with Honsel leading it.

28:53.819 --> 28:55.734
- I'm sorry.
Who am I talking to here?

28:55.777 --> 28:56.952
- As a courtesy to you,

28:56.996 --> 28:58.562
because I do cherish
your collaboration,

28:58.606 --> 29:01.522
I am letting you know
that we are not giving up

29:01.565 --> 29:05.700
on this case until we have
a drug supplier in custody.

29:05.744 --> 29:07.702
- Should I get the director
of FBI on the phone?

29:07.746 --> 29:08.790
- Call him.

29:08.834 --> 29:10.096
I'm sure he'd love to hear

29:10.139 --> 29:11.445
that a private security firm
is running point

29:11.488 --> 29:12.838
on an international
investigation.

29:12.881 --> 29:15.841
In fact,
I will call him myself.

29:15.884 --> 29:22.848
♪

29:31.552 --> 29:32.814
- Perhaps
you could give me an update

29:32.858 --> 29:34.773
on your investigation?

29:36.600 --> 29:38.820
- We have Tanja Kessler,

29:38.864 --> 29:41.170
the last person
to see Thomas Watts alive.

29:41.214 --> 29:42.737
She denied giving him
the drugs,

29:42.781 --> 29:45.435
but it was in her best interest
to do so.

29:45.479 --> 29:47.046
- She pointed the finger
at someone out of town

29:47.089 --> 29:49.875
who supplied the oxys
that led us to Finn Mueller.

29:49.918 --> 29:52.094
He's an admissions advisor
at DAAD.

29:52.138 --> 29:53.530
- And Finn Mueller led us

29:53.574 --> 29:55.576
to a drug-ordering app,
Black Penguin.

29:55.619 --> 29:57.230
Now he claims he didn't
give the app to Thomas,

29:57.273 --> 29:59.754
but because we don't have
his phone, we can't confirm it.

29:59.798 --> 30:01.843
- Where are we on the phone?

30:01.887 --> 30:05.455
- We are arranging
for its transfer.

30:06.979 --> 30:09.677
- So you are speaking directly
with Gray Desert?

30:09.720 --> 30:12.071
- We welcome the assistance
of outside entities,

30:12.114 --> 30:15.117
such as yourself,
who can help us bring this case

30:15.161 --> 30:17.903
to a firm resolution.

30:20.862 --> 30:22.472
- Should we try the app?

30:22.516 --> 30:24.213
- We should. Fire it up.

30:26.041 --> 30:29.001
[suspenseful music]

30:29.044 --> 30:33.135
♪

30:33.179 --> 30:35.137
- Okay, Finn Mueller.

30:42.188 --> 30:43.667
- Ask for a menu.

30:53.939 --> 30:55.854
- 10 blues, 5 snow?

31:00.249 --> 31:01.947
- Tell 'em
it has to be tonight.

31:01.990 --> 31:08.997
♪

31:14.220 --> 31:16.831
Okay, Raines, Vo,
you collect the drugs.

31:16.875 --> 31:18.528
Kellett, you and me
will keep a distance,

31:18.572 --> 31:20.052
follow the delivery man,
let him lead us

31:20.095 --> 31:21.662
to a stash house
or the supplier.

31:21.705 --> 31:24.708
And then joint bust, okay?

31:24.752 --> 31:26.841
- Yes. Okay.

31:26.885 --> 31:29.626
[speaking German]

31:29.670 --> 31:36.677
♪

31:41.334 --> 31:44.728
[indistinct chatter]

31:57.785 --> 31:59.221
- There's nothing out here.

32:01.876 --> 32:04.226
[phone buzzing]

32:07.751 --> 32:08.970
- Exit the club.

32:09.014 --> 32:11.103
You will see a park
across the street.

32:11.146 --> 32:13.627
- We're on the move.

32:17.022 --> 32:19.328
- I see you. Go into the park.

32:19.372 --> 32:26.596
♪

32:43.831 --> 32:45.093
- We're made.

32:45.137 --> 32:47.008
[tense music]

32:47.052 --> 32:48.227
- Get down on the ground!

32:48.270 --> 32:49.706
- [grunting]

32:49.750 --> 32:52.274
[sirens wailing]

32:52.318 --> 32:53.928
- Get him up!

32:53.972 --> 32:55.060
- Turn around!

32:55.103 --> 32:56.365
- Don't you move!
- I got him!

32:56.409 --> 32:58.193
- Hey, hey, hey, hey, hey!
What are you doing?

32:58.237 --> 32:59.803
- Executing our assignment.

32:59.847 --> 33:01.675
- This is just a delivery man!

33:01.718 --> 33:03.024
Are you serious right now?

33:03.068 --> 33:04.373
- You compromised our bust!

33:04.417 --> 33:06.897
- He almost got away.
You should be thanking me.

33:06.941 --> 33:09.248
- For ruining our only chance
of trailing him to the source?

33:09.291 --> 33:10.771
- There is your source.

33:10.814 --> 33:12.773
[zip ties clicking]

33:12.816 --> 33:19.823
♪

33:27.527 --> 33:29.485
- [speaking German]

33:29.529 --> 33:32.227
- This is absolutely
ridiculous.

33:32.271 --> 33:34.229
[tense music]

33:34.273 --> 33:35.665
This makes no sense to me.

33:35.709 --> 33:37.972
Okay, you know what,
let me ask you one question.

33:38.016 --> 33:39.669
- How did you work
in Narcotics for five years

33:39.713 --> 33:42.455
and not know you don't report
a police operation

33:42.498 --> 33:43.934
to a private security firm?

33:43.978 --> 33:45.806
- I assure you,
I was just keeping them

33:45.849 --> 33:47.416
up-to-date
with the investigation

33:47.460 --> 33:49.331
so we may not
cross-purpose our efforts!

33:49.375 --> 33:50.550
- Senior Chief Inspector,

33:50.593 --> 33:52.856
we understand
your position here.

33:52.900 --> 33:54.858
A giant international spotlight

33:54.902 --> 33:56.730
is pointing right
at the narcotics unit

33:56.773 --> 33:58.384
you run here in Berlin.

33:58.427 --> 33:59.863
The quicker
that spotlight goes away,

33:59.907 --> 34:02.040
the better for you
to keep everyone thinking

34:02.083 --> 34:04.520
you know what you're doing.

34:04.564 --> 34:08.394
But your incompetence has made
things infinitely worse

34:08.437 --> 34:10.874
this time.

34:10.918 --> 34:13.616
- If you'll excuse me,

34:13.660 --> 34:15.053
I've a confession to obtain.

34:15.096 --> 34:17.316
- Of course. Absolutely.

34:19.535 --> 34:21.015
- Guys, we have an update.

34:21.059 --> 34:22.930
- Levinson
turned Thomas' phone over

34:22.973 --> 34:24.714
to the Bundespolizei.

34:24.758 --> 34:26.629
Confirmed, the Black Penguin
app was on it.

34:26.673 --> 34:28.718
- Any record of Thomas
using the app last Friday?

34:28.762 --> 34:31.330
- Ordered a dozen oxy.
- That's it then.

34:31.373 --> 34:33.419
- And the pills
the delivery guy had on him,

34:33.462 --> 34:34.637
cut with fentanyl.

34:34.681 --> 34:36.465
The same batch
Thomas must have taken.

34:36.509 --> 34:37.988
- And what is the delivery man
saying?

34:38.032 --> 34:40.774
- The usual: he knows nothing,
the pills were planted.

34:40.817 --> 34:42.558
Says he's never heard
of Thomas Watts

34:42.602 --> 34:44.386
or the Black Penguin app.

34:44.430 --> 34:46.910
- Thank you.
Thanks very much.

34:46.954 --> 34:53.961
♪

34:55.180 --> 34:58.400
Agent Forrester,
no hard feelings, I hope.

35:00.315 --> 35:02.012
Mr. and Mrs. Watts wanted me
to assure you

35:02.056 --> 35:05.059
they're happy justice
was served.

35:05.103 --> 35:07.975
However we got there,
I'm just glad we got there.

35:08.018 --> 35:09.629
- Will you be leaving Berlin
then?

35:09.672 --> 35:11.283
- Yeah,
family wants to get back.

35:11.326 --> 35:13.285
Start making
funeral arrangements.

35:13.328 --> 35:15.069
- What's it been,
uh, three, four days

35:15.113 --> 35:16.940
since you've been here?

35:16.984 --> 35:18.464
- We landed Thursday.

35:20.857 --> 35:24.644
- Well, give the Wattses
my sincere condolences.

35:24.687 --> 35:26.385
- Appreciate that.

35:26.428 --> 35:33.435
♪

35:43.880 --> 35:45.926
- They got there ahead of us.
- What?

35:45.969 --> 35:48.102
- Thomas kept a secret
apartment in Kreuzberg.

35:48.146 --> 35:49.625
Secret even from his parents.

35:49.669 --> 35:51.975
But Levinson was there
before we arrived,

35:52.019 --> 35:53.629
confiscating the phone
and the laptop.

35:53.673 --> 35:55.805
- The German police
were sharing info with him.

35:55.849 --> 35:57.067
Honsel admitted it.

35:57.111 --> 35:58.895
- But Vo and you discovered
that location.

35:58.939 --> 36:00.375
Kellett and I went straight
to that apartment.

36:00.419 --> 36:02.334
How could they have gotten
there before us

36:02.377 --> 36:04.074
when only we knew the address?

36:04.118 --> 36:05.641
We checked the cameras outside

36:05.685 --> 36:07.034
of the party apartment
in Mitte, right?

36:07.077 --> 36:08.470
- Right.
- I wanna see if there

36:08.514 --> 36:09.993
are cameras outside
of the secret apartment

36:10.037 --> 36:12.170
in Kreuzberg, and I wanna know
who visited Thomas there

36:12.213 --> 36:15.347
up until the time he left
for that party.

36:15.390 --> 36:21.918
♪

36:33.669 --> 36:37.499
I'm gonna need you to answer
a few questions.

36:37.543 --> 36:38.674
- I'm sorry, I thought--

36:38.718 --> 36:40.720
- Not you.

36:40.763 --> 36:42.374
Him.

36:45.159 --> 36:47.683
That's you,
11:00 p.m. Thursday night,

36:47.727 --> 36:50.904
walking up to Thomas'
secret apartment in Kreuzberg.

36:53.907 --> 36:55.517
- No, that is not me.

36:55.561 --> 36:57.127
- Oh, you need a better angle?

36:57.171 --> 37:01.523
Here's one
from the ATM across the street.

37:01.567 --> 37:03.090
- Okay, fine. So what?

37:03.133 --> 37:04.787
- Why were you
at Thomas' apartment

37:04.831 --> 37:06.093
the same night that you

37:06.136 --> 37:07.834
and the Wattses flew in
from California?

37:07.877 --> 37:10.489
- Because I have been
with this family for 15 years,

37:10.532 --> 37:12.055
and I have great fondness
for Thomas.

37:12.099 --> 37:14.188
- So you told his parents
you were gonna see their son

37:14.232 --> 37:15.842
at his secret apartment
on the night you arrived?

37:15.885 --> 37:17.017
- I've no idea.
I don't remember.

37:17.060 --> 37:18.627
Everybody had jet lag.

37:18.671 --> 37:20.803
- Finn Mueller told us
he never gave Thomas the app.

37:20.847 --> 37:23.110
- And Tanja Kessler said he had
someone in town he knew

37:23.153 --> 37:25.808
who hooked him up.

37:25.852 --> 37:28.115
Someone he knew.
- Well, that's not me.

37:28.158 --> 37:30.248
- You kept that phone until
you knew where we were going

37:30.291 --> 37:31.553
with our investigation.

37:31.597 --> 37:32.728
Then you downloaded the app

37:32.772 --> 37:34.426
and pointed the finger
at Black Penguin.

37:34.469 --> 37:35.688
- No way. You have the guy.

37:35.731 --> 37:36.950
You found the drugs
on the dealer.

37:36.993 --> 37:38.908
- The baggie you pulled out
of his pocket?

37:38.952 --> 37:41.215
- I have the full capacity

37:41.259 --> 37:44.436
of the Federal Bureau
of Investigation behind me.

37:44.479 --> 37:45.828
Now, how long
do you think it's gonna take

37:45.872 --> 37:47.830
until I know exactly when
that app was downloaded

37:47.874 --> 37:49.484
on his phone?

37:49.528 --> 37:53.793
♪

37:53.836 --> 37:56.143
- I want a lawyer.

37:56.186 --> 37:57.927
[door clicks open]
- How could you?

37:57.971 --> 37:59.102
- It was an accident!
I didn't know!

37:59.146 --> 38:00.756
- How could you?

38:00.800 --> 38:01.888
How could you?

38:01.931 --> 38:03.629
- [speaking German]
- It was my son!

38:03.672 --> 38:04.630
- Mr. Watts!
- Come on, Mr. Watts.

38:04.673 --> 38:07.285
- No!
- It was an accident.

38:07.328 --> 38:08.547
- [yells]
- I'm sorry.

38:08.590 --> 38:09.591
- Get him out of here!
- Mr. Watts!

38:09.635 --> 38:11.724
- That was my son!
That was my son!

38:14.117 --> 38:18.948
- However we got there,
I'm glad we got there.

38:18.992 --> 38:21.560
[cuffs clinking]

38:22.909 --> 38:24.867
- I owe you an apology.

38:24.911 --> 38:27.653
- No, you were doing your job.
Same as me.

38:27.696 --> 38:28.915
- Well, as a diplomat,

38:28.958 --> 38:31.134
I could use lessons
in diplomacy from you.

38:31.178 --> 38:32.527
- Ha.

38:32.571 --> 38:34.137
No, you were caught
in a tough position.

38:38.664 --> 38:41.101
- If there
is anything you need,

38:41.144 --> 38:43.495
please don't hesitate to call.

38:43.538 --> 38:47.107
- You know what,
actually, there is something.

38:47.150 --> 38:49.979
How well do you know
the higher-ups in Europol?

38:50.023 --> 38:53.069
[pensive music]

38:53.113 --> 39:00.076
♪

39:00.120 --> 39:01.556
- I don't know how you did it.

39:01.600 --> 39:03.166
- Did what?

39:03.210 --> 39:06.082
- I was fired today
while you were reinstated.

39:06.126 --> 39:08.607
The executive director said
there was political pressure

39:08.650 --> 39:11.131
to remove me and keep you.

39:11.174 --> 39:13.263
Katrin, what did you do?

39:13.307 --> 39:15.701
- Good.

39:15.744 --> 39:19.574
[singing in German]

39:19.618 --> 39:25.711
♪

39:25.754 --> 39:28.322
- Yes, ma'am. Thank you, ma'am.

39:28.366 --> 39:30.063
No, of course,
I know what this means.

39:30.106 --> 39:32.848
Again, thank you.
I really appreciate it.

39:32.892 --> 39:34.154
- Who was that?

39:34.197 --> 39:35.808
- Remember when we saved
the attorney general

39:35.851 --> 39:37.200
from that assassination
attempt?

39:37.244 --> 39:38.941
- Of course.
- Well, Forrester and I

39:38.985 --> 39:42.641
have been working
on multiple fronts to--

39:42.684 --> 39:44.686
Mr. and Mrs. Watts,
thank you for coming.

39:44.730 --> 39:46.384
- I don't understand
why we're here.

39:46.427 --> 39:48.124
- Yes, I'm sorry
for the scant information,

39:48.168 --> 39:49.604
but I wanted to be sure.

39:49.648 --> 39:51.389
- Be sure of what?
- Thomas kept a partition

39:51.432 --> 39:53.913
on his laptop
where he created a pseudonym

39:53.956 --> 39:56.698
for his artwork social media.

39:56.742 --> 39:58.961
He wanted people to see him
for his art

39:59.005 --> 40:00.789
and not his name.

40:02.965 --> 40:05.925
[soft emotional music]

40:05.968 --> 40:09.319
♪

40:09.363 --> 40:11.060
- These are his paintings.

40:11.104 --> 40:18.111
♪

40:58.368 --> 41:01.328
[dramatic music]

41:01.371 --> 41:08.378
♪

41:17.866 --> 41:19.433
[wolf howls]
